{"bookId": "68f1ce4cc729e5251bd00430", "moduleId": "68f8d5406d5eb44aa9cc2c1f", "subjectId": "68f8d5cc6d5eb44aa9cc2c5e", "chapterId": "68f8d5e16d5eb44aa9cc2c6c", "subject": "Physics", "chapter": "Experimental Physics", "count": 4, "questions": [{"id": 312040, "subject": "Physics", "chapter": "Experimental Physics", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "Most Important Selected Qs for JEE Advanced", "q": "The main scale of a vernier callipers reads in millimeter and its vernier is divided into 10 divisions which coincides with 9 divisions of the main scale. The reading for shown situation is found to be $\\frac{12 \\mathrm{x}}{10} \\mathrm{~mm}$. Find the value of x .\n<img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/modules/ms/ja/fmwn0I3t80MjFiU2HdbwYsqOJuZfPSJQfZaZ1mSgXP4.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/modules/ms/ja/NP2GgslshAP58GHRy7CciIek7pTw-FBtffh4MdEt3U0.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>", "options": ["A", "B", "C", "D"], "answer": 0, "solution": "$\\begin{aligned} & \\text { Least count }=\\frac{1 \\mathrm{~mm}}{10}=0.1 \\mathrm{~mm} \\text {; Zero error }=-(10-6) \\times 0.1=-0.4 \\mathrm{~mm} \\\\ & \\text { Reading }=6+5 \\times(0.1)-(-0.4)=7.2 \\mathrm{~mm}\\end{aligned}$", "difficulty": "Easy", "source": "Most Important Selected Qs for JEE Advanced", "_book": "68f1ce4cc729e5251bd00430", "_chapterKey": "68f1ce4cc729e5251bd00430__68f8d5406d5eb44aa9cc2c1f__68f8d5cc6d5eb44aa9cc2c5e__68f8d5e16d5eb44aa9cc2c6c"}, {"id": 312041, "subject": "Physics", "chapter": "Experimental Physics", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "Most Important Selected Qs for JEE Advanced", "q": "The length of a cylinder is measured with a metre rod having least count 0.1 cm . Its diameter is measured with vernier callipers having least count 0.01 cm . Given the length is 5.0 cm and diameter is 2.00 cm . Find the percentage error in the calculated value of volume.", "options": ["A", "B", "C", "D"], "answer": 0, "solution": "$\\mathrm{V}=\\pi \\mathrm{r}^2 \\mathrm{~h}=\\frac{\\pi \\mathrm{D}^2 \\mathrm{~h}}{4} \\Rightarrow \\frac{\\Delta \\mathrm{~V}}{\\mathrm{~V}}=\\frac{2 \\Delta \\mathrm{D}}{\\mathrm{D}}+\\frac{\\Delta \\mathrm{h}}{\\mathrm{h}} \\frac{\\Delta \\mathrm{V}}{\\mathrm{V}} \\times 100=\\left[2 \\times\\left(\\frac{0.01}{2.00}\\right)+\\left(\\frac{0.1}{5.0}\\right)\\right] \\times 100=3 \\%$", "difficulty": "Easy", "source": "Most Important Selected Qs for JEE Advanced", "_book": "68f1ce4cc729e5251bd00430", "_chapterKey": "68f1ce4cc729e5251bd00430__68f8d5406d5eb44aa9cc2c1f__68f8d5cc6d5eb44aa9cc2c5e__68f8d5e16d5eb44aa9cc2c6c"}, {"id": 312042, "subject": "Physics", "chapter": "Experimental Physics", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "Most Important Selected Qs for JEE Advanced", "q": "Time period of a simple pendulum is given by $\\mathrm{T}=2 \\pi \\sqrt{\\frac{\\ell}{g}}$ where $\\ell$ is the length of pendulum and g is acceleration due to gravity. If percentage increase in the length and acceleration due to gravity are $69 \\%$ and $21 \\%$ respectively then find out percentage increase in time period.", "options": ["A", "B", "C", "D"], "answer": 0, "solution": "$\\frac{\\mathrm{T}^{\\prime}-\\mathrm{T}}{\\mathrm{T}} \\times 100=\\left(\\sqrt{\\frac{\\ell^{\\prime} \\mathrm{g}}{\\ell \\mathrm{g}^{\\prime}}}-1\\right) \\times 100=\\left(\\sqrt{\\frac{1.69}{1.21}}-1\\right) \\times 100=\\left(\\frac{1.3}{1.1}-1\\right) \\times 100=\\frac{0.2}{1.1} \\times 100=\\frac{200}{11}=18.18 \\%$", "difficulty": "Medium", "source": "Most Important Selected Qs for JEE Advanced", "_book": "68f1ce4cc729e5251bd00430", "_chapterKey": "68f1ce4cc729e5251bd00430__68f8d5406d5eb44aa9cc2c1f__68f8d5cc6d5eb44aa9cc2c5e__68f8d5e16d5eb44aa9cc2c6c"}, {"id": 312043, "subject": "Physics", "chapter": "Experimental Physics", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "Most Important Selected Qs for JEE Advanced", "q": "A screw gauge with a pitch of <math><mn>1</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&nbsp;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m<